Dollar, Yen Weaken as Asian Stocks Extend Gain, Reducing Demand for Safety

-- B y   M a s a k i   K o n d o
-- 
2011-09-27T02:43:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/dollar-yen-weaken-as-asian-stocks-extend-gain-reducing-demand-for-safety.html
The dollar extended declines
against the euro and fell against 15 of its 16 major
counterparts.  The dollar dropped to $1.3559 per euro as of 11:41 a.m. in
 Tokyo  from $1.3533 yesterday in  New York . The yen also slid
against most major peers as Asian stocks extended gains.   To contact the reporter on this story:
